cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to person re-identification, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes an end-to-end network architecture for foreground-aware person re-identification, which involves learning a soft mask to distinguish foreground from background. This involves optimizing both foreground and background branches, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the proposed method on three challenging datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
